<h3>What is a Juice Cleanse?</h3>
<p>A juice cleanse is a set period of time where people drink fresh juice to reduce stress on their digestive systems. At it's core, a juice cleanse is about rest and rejuvenation of mind, body, and spirit. More than just a quick fix, cleansing is a way to start developing practices that lead to lasting health. Cleanses can be as simple as replacing a single meal with a bottle of juice, or replacing several days of solid food in favor of feasting on organic, freshly pressed juice. </p><br>
<h3>Why should I do a cleanse?</h3>
<p>Over time, our bodies accumulate toxins from pollutants in the air, chemicals, processed foods, and stress. With all of the demands in our modern world, it's important to take the time to release these toxins, as they can lead to both physical and mental imbalances. By taking a break from eating solid foods, your body is free to direct all the energy that is usually uses for digesting food, into targeting and healing specific conditions. The truth is that our body is amazing at healing, when it has the resources and time to do so. During our cleanse, you’ll be flooding your system with pounds of fresh, organic juice each day. The live enzymes and minerals found in our juice allow your body to heal and recharge, while essential nutrients are absorbed directly into your bloodstream. This results in immediate nutrition, designed to detoxify and nourish your entire body.</p>
<p>Whether you’re doing a juice cleanse to jumpstart a new diet or using it as a gateway into a healthier lifestyle; our cleanses are all about becoming more in tune with your body. When used mindfully, they are a powerful tool into experiencing balance, mental clarity, and rejuvenating energy! </p><br>
<h3>Can I go to work while cleansing?</h3>
<p>Yes. It’s a common misconception that you will spend the duration of your cleanse either lounging with cucumber slices over your eyes, or running for the bathroom every hour. Fortunately, this is not the case. If you prepare yourself properly, you should be able to go about your normal life. However, it’s best to schedule your cleanse during a time where you can listen to your body’s needs and follow them. Your busiest and most stressful week of the year would not be the ideal time for a cleanse!</p>
<h3>Can I cleanse while pregnant?</h3>
<p>No. You should not cleanse because you need to add more calories while pregnant or nursing. You also do not want to have your body go into detox mode and release toxins into your bloodstream. However, adding our fresh organic juice to your daily diet is an excellent way to provide essential vitamins, minerals and living enzymes to keep you and your baby healthy during this important time. </p><br>
<h3>Can I exercise during a cleanse?</h3>
<p>Absolutely! If you feel good and want to exercise, do so! You are still sustaining enough of a caloric load to keep your body and mind functioning. Above all, it's important to listen to your body. </p>
<p>Your energy will most definitely fluctuate during a cleanse. Some days you will feel on top of the world and bursting with energy, other days you may feel run down and in need of rest. Be sure to note your energy levels and adjust accordingly. Light exercise such as walking, yoga, and swimming are great ways to boost circulation and support the cleanse process. </p><br>
