<h3>How will I feel during my cleanse?</h3>
<p>
The cleansing process is a very personal experience and varies between person to person. Whether this is your first cleanse or your tenth, each experience is unique. How you will feel during a cleanse largely depends on your current diet, lifestyle factors and well as your own biological makeup. Most people experience some sort of detox reaction during the initial phase of a cleanse. Common detoxification symptoms include fatigue, headaches or mild skin breakouts as your body begins purging toxins. This is a natural part of the process, and although unpleasant, a sign that the cleanse is working. The bulk of these are experienced in the first 24-36 hours; treat yourself kindly and give yourself time and space to rest. After this period, most people claim to feel more vibrant and emotionally alive. You may also experience feelings of euphoria, total mental clarity and super-heightened senses.
</p>
<h3>How many days should I cleanse?</h3>
<p>Ultimately, that depends on your personal experience and health goals. Bloom Juice Co. gives you the option to cleanse for 1, 3, 5, 7 or 10 days which we feel are realistic and achievable. We want you to have a positive experience while cleansing and making the transition into a healthier lifestyle. </p>
<p>If it's your first time, we recommend a 1 to 3 day cleanse as a good starting point. The more days you cleanse, the deeper you clean out your digestive tract while starting to rebuild and strengthen your immune system. It's very common for people to feel so good during their cleanse that they choose to continue for a longer period, in which case you can always extend with a 24 hour notice. </p><br>
<h3>When is the best time to cleanse?</h3>
<p>We recommend cleansing when you have very few distractions and feel you can commit fully to the cleanse. Some things to consider are your experience, work schedule, and social commitments. Ideally, you do not want to cleanse during a high stress period. Give yourself plenty of time to relax, de stress, and focus on yourself. This is as much a mental and emotional experience as it is physical.</p><br>
<h3>How often can I cleanse?</h3>
<p>It really is a personal preference. Some people do a big cleanse once or twice a year, some people do it as a ritual one day a week to reset their bodies. In our experience, cleansing seasonally is wonderful way to maintain health during the changing seasons. As with everything, balance is key. We believe listening to your body is the best way of finding out what works for you.</p><br>
